| Operator | Description         | Syntax |
| -------- | ------------------- | ------ |
| &        | Bitwise AND         | x & y  |
| \|       | Bitwise OR          | x \| y |
| ~        | Bitwise NOT         | ~x     |
| ^        | Bitwise XOR         | x ^ y  |
| \>>      | Bitwise right shift | x>>    |
| <<       | Bitwise left shift  | x<<    |

Bitwise AND Operator
If the bits in the compared positions of the bit patterns are 1, then the resulting bit is 1. If not, it is 0.
Bitwise OR Operator
if the two bits in the looked-at position are 0, the next bit is zero. If not, it is 1.
Bitwise XOR Operator
If the bits are different, it returns 1; otherwise, it returns 0.
Bitwise NOT Operator
This means it toggles all bits in the value, transforming 0 bits to 1 and 1 bits to 0
Bitwise Right Shift
Shifts the bits of the number to the right and fills 0 on voids left( fills 1 in the case of a negative number)
as a result. Similar effect as of dividing the number with some power of two.
Bitwise Left Shift
Shifts the bits of the number to the left and fills 0 on voids right as a result. 
Similar effect as of multiplying the number with some power of two.
